 <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>, following the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Representatives </ORGANIZATION>, passed the Omnibus Trade Bill which contains provisions problematical for <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Obuchi </PERSON> stated. `` The government of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> strongly hopes that such a bill will not finally be enacted.'' On Wednesday, Japanese Prime Minister <PERSON> Noboru </PERSON> <PERSON> Takeshita </PERSON> also warned that the bill could damage the global economy, and said <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> would try to restrain growing protectionism in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> by improving its ties with <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>.
